Assuming `std::cerr` and `std::cout` both print to the terminal in order, what does this program print to `std::cout` (not `std::cerr`) when input is `6`?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int triple(int n)
{
    return n + n;
}

int main()
{
    int x;
    std::cin >> x;
    std::cerr << "x = " << x << "\n";
    std::cout << triple(x) << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```
